      • adjust

        public Coordinate adjust(Coordinate i)
        Description copied from class: Lattice
        The native coordinate system for eSLIME is Cartesian. That is, if we specify a rectangular geometry with width 10 and height 5, we expect this to be reflected as (roughly) a rectangle-shaped lattice, regardless of the lattice connectivity.

        However, some lattices do not have orthogonal bases. To make them consistent with a Cartesian coordinate system, it is necessary to adjust an incoming Cartesian coordinate to reflect their native coordinate system. That adjustment is supplied in the adjust(...) method.

        Specified by:
        adjust in class Lattice
        Parameters:
        i - -- a Cartesian coordinate.
        Returns:
        -- a coordinate in the native coordinate system.

      • getDisplacement

        public Coordinate getDisplacement(Coordinate pCoord,
                         Coordinate qCoord)
        Description copied from class: Lattice
        Get the displacement vector between the specified coordinates. The displacement vector is given in units of the lattice's basis vector. The displacement assumes infinite boundary conditions.

        In the event that the basis of the lattice is linearly dependent, as in the case of the triangular lattice, the displacement vector returned by this method should minimize the L1 distance. Linear independence of components can be enforced using getOrthoDisplacement().

        Specified by:
        getDisplacement in class Lattice
